Text.Value: He tried to stop me from inspecting the cargo.
I see Marls took... took a bit of a dive.
Just letting you know that your soldier's taken a dive into the lake.
Of course, True Soul! As you say.
They're not to be opened until they reach the city. The Absolute smiles on them that follow orders.
I see. Then you'd better fish your man out of the lake.
He was from the city, I think. Well... down there's his home now.
Tell me why you're shipping tadpoles to the city.
Leave.
Leave.
Fool. He always took orders too literally. Of course you can check the cargo.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little too quickly, sucking up to us.

Text.Value: We're not supposed to leave the cargo un-... oh.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trailing off as he realizes this is what got his comrade killed

Text.Value: Your soldier abandoned his post. You'd best go report it.
Just doing my job. They say the Absolute sees our work, and elevates the worthy.
Thank you.
I showed him the truth of the tadpoles you're shipping.
Aye, True Soul?
...Eh, respectfully, True Soul.
Tell me why you're shipping tadpoles to the city.
Ah, sorry True Soul. Cargo's been tampered with - I'd best see to it.
You definitely have the attitude of a True Soul, at least.
Leave.
Beg pardon, True Soul - but you're distracting me.
No, True Soul. Not I. Too busy doing my job. Which... I'll get back to, aye?
Aye?
Good riddance. He deserved it! ... whatever he did.

EditorData.NodeContext: Vehemently on our side - he does not want to piss us off like his ill-fated friend did. Last line a little uncertain.

Text.Value: And I don't plan on being a guard for long, True Soul.
What's so important about these boxes?
Please. Be my guest.
I'm not hearing much respect.
Stand clear of the cargo!
What? Beshaba's black bones - wait here. I'll find something to drag him out.
Tell me why you're shipping tadpoles to the city.
Not letting a decent suit of armour rot down there on my watch.
I'm just a soldier. Which, speaking of... I'd best go report my man missing. If you'll excuse me...
Are you much of a swimmer?
Leave.
...Tadpoles? Like... a delicacy? I wouldn't know much about that, True Soul.

Synopsis: Guard is watching operations at Moonrise Docks. If the other guard jumped into the water, the player can use it to send this last guard away so they can examine the cargo.
